---
import Layout from '../layouts/layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Dylan Purbrick | Cover Letter" activeTab="cover-letter">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <header class="mb-20 border-b border-slate-200 pb-12">
        <h1 class="text-6xl font-black uppercase tracking-tighter mb-4">Cover Letter</h1>
        <p class="text-brand-purple font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.4em]">Section_02 // Application Archive</p>
    </header>

    <div class="bg-white p-12 md:p-20 shadow-xl font-neue text-slate-800 leading-relaxed space-y-12">
        <div class="flex justify-between items-start border-b border-slate-100 pb-8">
            <div class="space-y-1">
                <p class="font-black uppercase text-xl text-industrial-black">Dylan Purbrick</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-slate-400">Mo. 0451 317 463 | Dylan.m.purbrick@gmail.com</p>
                <p class="text-xs font-mono text-slate-400">Bondi, NSW 2026</p>
            </div>
            <p class="text-xs font-mono text-slate-500">10/03/2026</p>
        </div>

        <div class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-500">
            <p>Industrus Engineering</p>
            <p>IndustrusEng.com.au</p>
            <p>Australia</p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6">
            <p class="font-black uppercase text-industrial-black tracking-tight">RE: GRADUATE ENGINEER PROGRAM APPLICATION</p>
            
            <p>Dear Hiring Manager,</p>
            
            <p>
                I am writing to apply for the Graduate Engineer Program at Industrus Engineering. I am currently finishing my final year of a Bachelor of Engineering (Honours) in Mechatronic Engineering at UTS while working as an Engineering Assistant at Keith Engineering[cite: 52, 53]. My professional journey is driven by a deep passion for mechanical systems and a belief that the best learning happens through hands-on experience[cite: 54].
            </p>

            <div class="space-y-6 pl-6 border-l-2 border-slate-100">
                <section>
                    <h3 class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-purple mb-2">Professional Accountability</h3>
                    <p>At Keith Engineering, I am often responsible for the final quality check of manufacturing drawings before they reach the fitting shop[cite: 56]. My task is to ensure every detail is technically accurate to prevent material waste or mechanical failure[cite: 57]. I systematically cross-reference every CAD model against its Bill of Materials (BOM) to catch discrepancies early[cite: 58]. This process has taught me that accountability isn't just about finishing a task, but about ensuring the final product is safe and efficient[cite: 60].</p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h3 class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-purple mb-2">Technical Communication</h3>
                    <p>My role requires me to act as a bridge between our technical drafting team and our clients[cite: 62]. I am tasked with taking technical site visit reports and summarizing them into clear project costs and customer quotes[cite: 63]. I translate complex engineering data into accessible information so that clients understand exactly what they are paying for[cite: 64].</p>
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h3 class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-purple mb-2">Innovation & Performance</h3>
                    <p>For a university project, I designed a functional, print-in-place set of pliers using additive manufacturing, utilizing tight tolerance control to ensure the rotational joint moved smoothly[cite: 68, 70]. Additionally, I recently developed a ROS 2 perception subsystem for an autonomous robot using OpenCV, achieving a 90% success rate during physical testing[cite: 74, 77].</p>
                </section>
            </div>

            <p>
                As a co-founder and Team Executive of the UTS MechSoc, I helped grow a society focused on professional development, overseen an executive team, and organized large-scale events[cite: 86, 87]. I am eager to bring this collaborative mindset and my hands-on background to the teams at Industrus[cite: 90].
            </p>

            <p>Thank you for taking the time to consider my application. I look forward to hearing from you.</p>

            <div class="pt-8">
                <p>Best Regards,</p>
                <p class="font-black uppercase text-xl">Dylan Purbrick</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
